I had a severe pain in my left shoulder following a gym injury, I was supposed to go under surgery. But I decided to take another opinion and after seeing reviews called Dr Amit. 
He asked me to come quickly to his clinic. He advised and gave me medications and helped me with the pain. It’s an ongoing treatment but still I am hopeful.

I had visited Dr.  Amit with broken shoulder and limited movement in my right hand. Before visiting him  ,  I was treated by so called best doctors and facilities in Australia and had spent  good amount of money on the treatment. But the situation was  not improving  and had limited movement around 15-20 % when I  visited him.  Within 10 days  I got almost all my movement back. I am much better now. The most amazing things about the whole treatment , he never asked me to go for  any Xray , CTScan or MRI.  I find him very honest , sincere ,  no rush attitude, friendly and very helpful.  He helped me with my  neck problem too.  He seems to be very well read and all round abilities  to guide the patient for right treatment. Highly recommended.

review_reply.reply_text: Great to learn that you are doing good.

survey_response.review_text: I sprained my ankle during badminton in UK. After that I started getting numbness in my leg. I could not stand or walk for more than 10 minutes. I was in continous pain. I have consulted many doctors in UK, undergone physio theraphy, acupuncture. But nothing helped. I have specially visited India get my whole body check up. I have consulted couple of doctors there too. Accidently I met Dr. Amit in Gurudwara during his service there.He is the one who gave me hope and diagnosed correct MRI and found the root cause of my pain. I am very  greatful to him. Following his advice and physio theraphy sessions I am feeling much better in long long time. I strongly recommend Dr. Amit for any ortho/spine related issues.  Thank you!

My mother visited Dr. Agarwal for pain and sourness in her heel. First thing very appreciable and professional about Dr. Agarwal was that he called me much before the appointment time and informed me that he is going to be half an hour late as he is stuck in some medical emergency case and he asked me if that's ok. And when we reached clinic there were already few patients in queue before us but the receptionist informed him about our situation and we were let in earlier than them. So, Dr. Agarwal respects his patient's time which is not the case with many doctors. His check up was also good and he explained the issue also in detail. And another great thing about him is that when I faced cunfusion about his prescribed medicine then I called him which he didn't receive. But just after sometime I got a call back from him and he explained about the medicine very patiently. Very professional and helpful he is. Thank you sir.
